==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[convergere]]'', from ''[[con-#Latin|con-]]'', "together", + ''[[vergere]]'', "to bend".
===Verb===
'''to converge'''
# (''intransitive'') to approach each other; to get closer and closer
# (''intransitive''; ''mathematics'') (of a [[sequence]]) to have a [[limit]]
====Antonyms====
*to [[diverge]]
